&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;Akido builds AI-powered doctors&lt;strong&gt;.&lt;/strong&gt; Akido is the first AI-native care provider, combining cutting-edge technology with a nationwide medical network to address America’s physician shortage and make exceptional healthcare universal. Its AI empowers doctors to deliver faster, more accurate, and more compassionate care.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Serving 500K+ patients across California, Rhode Island, and New York, Akido offers primary and specialty care in 26 specialties—from serving&amp;nbsp;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.fastcompany.com/91231274/how-one-la-doctor-is-using-ai-to-help-homeless-communities-get-medical-care&quot;&gt;unhoused communities&lt;/a&gt;&amp;nbsp;in Los Angeles to&amp;nbsp;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.wsj.com/articles/the-ai-doctor-will-see-new-york-ride-share-drivers-now-5ba53e6c?mod=Searchresults_pos1&amp;amp;page=1&quot;&gt;ride-share drivers&lt;/a&gt;&amp;nbsp;in New York.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Founded in 2015 (YC W15), Akido is expanding its risk-bearing care models and scaling&amp;nbsp;ScopeAI, its breakthrough clinical AI platform. &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.businesswire.com/news/home/20250515102298/en/Akido-Raises-%2460-Million-Series-B-to-Expand-Reach-of-ScopeAI-its-Breakthrough-Health-Artificial-Intelligence&quot;&gt;Read more about Akido’s $60M Series B&lt;/a&gt;. More info at &lt;a href=&quot;http://Akidolabs.com&quot;&gt;Akidolabs.com&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;The Opportunity&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We’re building something new for New York City’s independent drivers — the people who keep the city moving but are often left out of traditional healthcare systems. Together with the &lt;a href=&quot;https://driversguild.org/&quot;&gt;Independent Drivers Guild&lt;/a&gt; and the &lt;a href=&quot;https://workersbenefitfund.com/&quot;&gt;Workers Benefit Fund (WBF)&lt;/a&gt;, we launched the &lt;a href=&quot;https://workerhealthyliving.org/&quot;&gt;Worker Healthy Living Program&lt;/a&gt; (WHLP) — a lifestyle medicine–informed program focused on helping drivers live healthier, longer lives through food, movement, sleep, stress management, and community.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We’re looking for a &lt;strong&gt;Physician (MD or DO)&lt;/strong&gt; who believes that health starts with lifestyle and relationships — not just prescriptions. This role is for a physician who wants to blend clinical care with hands-on program design, patient connection, and health education.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;This isn’t a typical primary care role.&lt;/strong&gt; You’ll join a small, collaborative care team — including advanced practice clinicians, a dietitian, health coach, social worker, and medical assistant — working across in-person and virtual settings. You’ll lead and support shared medical visits, guide patients through six-month lifestyle medicine programs, and provide clinical leadership and oversight for group-based care focused on nutrition, physical activity, stress reduction, restorative sleep, and social connection.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Beyond direct care, you’ll help shape how the model runs — refining workflows, advising on clinical protocols, and co-creating a system that supports both patients and providers. You’ll also work with Akido’s AI-powered platform to make care easier and more personalized — using technology to reduce administrative burden and enhance, not replace, the human connection.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Telehealth is a core part of how we deliver care.&lt;/strong&gt; This role offers up to 2 days per week of remote/telehealth work (subject to clinic needs and scheduling), giving you real flexibility while staying connected to your patients and care team. We know today’s physicians value the ability to work from home — and we’ve built that into how we operate, not as an afterthought, but as part of our model.&lt;/p&gt;
